  "texts": [
    "We can express the policy gradients of ω and θ in the closed form below [Sutton et al., 1999].∇ ω J l (ϕ ω, µ) = E π,ϕ,P µ r l (s, b, µ) + γV ϕω,µ l (s ′) -V ϕω,µ l (s) ∇ ω log ϕ ω (b | s), ∇ θ J f (π θ, ϕ, µ)=E π,ϕ,P µ r f (s, a, b, µ)-τ log π(a | s)+γV π θ,ϕ,µ f (s ′)-V π θ,ϕ,µ f (s) ∇ θ log π θ (a|s).The policy updates ( 7), (8) of Algorithm 2 are exactly based on the policy gradient expressions above, substituting in the latest leader's policy parameter ω k, follower's policy parameter θ k, and mean field iterate μk.",
    "Here the value functions are defined asV ϕ,µ l (s)=E[ ∞ k γ k r l (s, b, µ)|s 0 =s], V π,ϕ,µ f (s)=E[ ∞ k γ k (r f (s, a, b, µ)-τ log π(a | s))|s 0 =s].Algorithm 1 requires access toV ϕω k,μ k l and V π θ k,ϕω k,μ k ffor policy gradient evaluation.",
    "Since these value functions are not directly available, we estimate them by V l,k and V f,k, which are updated via temporal difference (TD) learning in (10).",
    "Note that to ensure stability we leverage projections in ( 9) and ( 10): Π ∆ S denotes the projection to the probability simplex over the state space, and Π B V denotes the element-wise projection to the interval [0, B V], whereB V = 1/(1 -γ) + τ log |A|.Our method exemplifies independent learning in the sense that ω k, θ k, μk are each updated to optimize its own objective without any knowledge of the other two, though the samples used for the updates are from an environment determined by all variables.",
    "We note that the algorithm is single-loop and uses two trajectories of continuously generated samplesfoot_0, making it significantly more practical than the existing methods with complex nested loops [Dayanıklı andLaurière, 2024, Cui et al., 2024].Algorithm 1 Single loop Actor-Critic Algorithm for Stackelberg Mean Field Games (AC-SMFG) 1: Initialize: leader's policy parameter ω 0, follower's policy parameter θ 0, value function estimates Vl,0, Vf,0, mean field estimate μ0 ∈ ∆ S, initial state s 0, s0 ∼ ρ, step sizesζ k ≤ ξ k ≤ α k ≤ β k. 2: for iteration k = 0, 1, 2,... do 3:Sample path 1 for tracking the discounted occupancy measure: Follower and leader take actions Leader's policy update:a k ∼ π θ k (• | s k), b k ∼ ϕ ω k (• | s k), receive rewards r f (s k, a k, b k, μk),ω k+1 = ω k + ζ k ∇ ω log ϕ ω k (b k | s k) r l (s k, b k, μk) + γ Vl,k (s k+1) -Vl,k (s k)(7) 6:Follower's policy (actor) update:θ k+1 =θ k +α k ∇ θ log π θ k (a k |s k) r f (s k, a k, b k, μk)+τ E(π θ k, s k)+γ Vf,k (s k+1)-Vf,k (s k)(8) 7:Mean field update:μk+1 = Π ∆ S μk + ξ k (e sk -μk)(9) 8:Value function (critic) update:Vl,k+1 = Π B V Vl,k + β k e s k r l (s k, b k, μk) + γ Vl,k (s k+1) -Vl,k (s k) (10) Vf,k+1 =Π B V Vf,k +β k e s k r f (s k, a k, b k, μk) + τ E(π θ k, s k) + γ Vf,k (s k+1) -Vf,k (s k) 9: end for Convergence AnalysisIn this section, we establish the convergence of AC-SMFG."
  ],
